200. ipsae] ‘by themselves’, i.e. without the male. The same account is given, among others, by Aristotle. As a matter of fact, the queen bee is fertilized from a drone, and then lays eggs at the rate of at least two hundred a day, which are then taken 111 charge by some of the working bees. In five days the larvae are developed, spin for themselves a cocoon‚ and are transformed into pupae, from which the perfect insect is hatched in seven or eight days.
